    <!--
      Flowdometer Reporting (View Only).

      The least-privilege half of the Flowdometer access model. Grants read +
      View All on the package's own tracking objects (Flow__c, Listener__c,
      Step__c) and visibility of the reporting tabs/dashboards, so a user can
      see cross-team Flowdometer data WITHOUT the ability to create Listeners
      (which is the elevated, schema-changing capability — that lives in
      Flowdometer_User / the permission set group).

      Deliberately omits: object create/edit/delete, Modify All, the Setup tab,
      Apex class accesses, and the Feature_Flag CMDT. A holder of this set alone
      cannot create a Listener (no create permission on Listener__c — the
      controller's isCreateable() gate and the DML both fail), so no schema
      change can be triggered. Assign individually to view-only users, or assign
      the Flowdometer_Access permission set group for full access.

      Note: the dynamically created lookup fields carry FLS on the runtime
      unmanaged permission set (Flowdometer_Dynamic_FLS), so a Reporting-only
      user sees all packaged fields but not those dynamic lookup values; assign
      the permission set group for full visibility including dynamic fields.
    -->
